Description
===========

CoStLy is a free library of complex interval standard functions. 


Installation
============

1) Make sure you have

	a) the GNU C++ compiler gcc 2.95.2

	b) the filib++ library (version 2.0)
	   OR
	   the C-XSC library (version 2.0 beta)
	   
   installed.

2) Unpack the sources with the command "tar -xvzf <packagename.tgz>".
   This creates a directory ./<packagename> with all the necessary files.

3) For use of CoStLy with the filib++ library compile with the preprocessor
   option "-DFILIB_VERSION".
   For use with the CXSC library compile without the above option.

Notice on point 1)
==================

You can download both the C-XSC library and the filib++ library from

http://www.xsc.de

To install the libraries see the respective README files.

Technical support
=================

None. CoStLy is free software, remember?

In case of trouble, you may try sending an email to one of the above adresses,
with fingers crossed for reply.
